- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with triangulations and distance computation between piecewise linear functions, which are common topics in computational geometry. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for numerical computation of distances between functions. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents an algorithmic approach to the problem. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves polynomial evaluation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the least likely category as the paper does not seem to deal with control systems or feedback control.
